
**What They Do:**
- Define upgrade metadata (name, description, icon, rarity values)
- Contain `apply(player, values)` method that modifies player
- Determine how stat increases scale with rarity

**Example Flow - DamageUpgrade:**
```javascript
apply(player, values) {
    const damageIncrease = values.damage || values[this.id] || values.common;
    player.damage = (player.damage || 1) + damageIncrease;  // Uses accessor!
}

